\begin_inset Formula $b_{a_{i}}$
\end_inset

 are auxiliaries.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Pro: quadratization symmetric in all non-auxiliary variables, which isn't
 true for all quadratizations of symmetric functions.
 Reproduces the full spectrum.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Con: all quadratic terms of the non-auxiliary variables, are non-submodular.
 Also very complicated and uses more auxiliaris than simlper methods.
\end_layout

